litematica_printer.config.comment.printe:
Whitelist of compostable items used for automatic composter filling.
You can enter an item ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:wheat§r §bWheat§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding items by tag), e.g.: §l#compostable§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lWheat,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first).
litematica_printer.config.comment.autoIn: Automatically enable remote container interaction if allowed by the server, otherwise disable it automatically
litematica_printer.config.comment.bedroc: Uses BedrockMiner mod to break bedrock (unavailable if BedrockMiner is not installed)
litematica_printer.config.comment.blockl:
You can enter a block ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:stone§r §bSandstone§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding blocks by tag), e.g.: §l#logs§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lGlazed Terracotta,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first; other methods are not yet implemented).
litematica_printer.config.comment.catego: Master category containing all configuration items; view/modify all printer-related settings
Bedrock breaking related configurations, integrating bedrock destruction functionality from the BedrockMiner mod
Printer interface highlight color settings (e.g., highlight colors for container sync and inventory addition)
Excavation mode related configurations, including excavation limits, whitelist/blacklist, breaking incorrect blocks and other excavation behavior settings
Core general settings of the printer, including basic configurations such as working interval, working radius, iteration rules
Shortcut key configurations for all printer functions, including hotkey bindings for printing, mode switching, container sync, etc.
Block placement related configurations, including placement cooldown, skip rules, easy place, ice breaking for water placement and other printing behavior settings
litematica_printer.config.comment.checkP:
When enabled, the printer only processes blocks within the PlayerBlockInteractionRange (player's block interaction distance).
Blocks beyond this range will not be printed/mined/filled to avoid cross-distance operations being detected by the server.
litematica_printer.config.comment.closeA: Close all modes; if in Single Mode, restore to Print mode
litematica_printer.config.comment.cloudI:
Supports remote container interaction if the server allows it or in single-player mode.
Replacement positions are the preset positions of the schematic.
litematica_printer.config.comment.debugO: When enabled, debug information will be output to the console
litematica_printer.config.comment.easyPl: Use Litematica's easy place protocol for block placement
litematica_printer.config.comment.excava:
Prevent mining blocks in this list (only effective in Excavation mode).
You can enter a block ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:stone§r §bSandstone§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding blocks by tag), e.g.: §l#logs§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lGlazed Terracotta,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first).

Filter type for excavation mode restrictions: None, Whitelist, Blacklist.
§dNone§r: No restrictions on any blocks
§dWhitelist§r: Only allow mining blocks in the whitelist
§dBlacklist§r: Prohibit mining blocks in the blacklist
§lThis setting is ignored when using Tweakeroo's excavation limit presets.§r

Use Tweakeroo's excavation limit presets or custom excavation limit presets.
§dTweakeroo Presets§r: Use Tweakeroo's excavation restriction presets
§dCustom§r: Use custom excavation restriction presets

Only allow mining blocks in this list (only effective in Excavation mode).
You can enter a block ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:stone§r §bSandstone§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding blocks by tag), e.g.: §l#logs§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lGlazed Terracotta,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first).
litematica_printer.config.comment.fill: Place blocks from the §6Fill Block List§r within the selection range
litematica_printer.config.comment.fillBl: List of blocks used in Fill mode. Enter item IDs or translated names (same rules as block lists)
Select the mode for filling blocks: Whitelist Mode (use items in the config list), Handheld Item Mode (use the item held in the main hand)
litematica_printer.config.comment.fillMo: Facing direction of blocks when filling (applies to slabs? stairs?)
litematica_printer.config.comment.fillSe:
Set the working selection range rules for the printer in Fill mode:
§dLitematica Selection§r: Use the full currently selected schematic selection as the working range
§dLitematica Render Layer§r: Only work within the current schematic render layer range
§dLitematica Selection (Below Player)§r: Only process areas below the player's height in the selection
§dLitematica Selection (Above Player)§r: Only process areas above the player's height in the selection
litematica_printer.config.comment.fluid: By default, place blocks from the §6Fluid Replacement Block List§r at lava/water sources
litematica_printer.config.comment.fluidB:
List of blocks used to replace fluids. Enter item IDs or translated names, e.g.: §bminecraft:sand§r §bSand§r.
Prefix with §b#§r for tag matching, e.g.: §l#sand§r.
litematica_printer.config.comment.fluidL: List of fluids to be replaced. Enter fluid IDs, e.g.: §bminecraft:water§r.
litematica_printer.config.comment.fluidM: Treat flowing fluids as part of the fill content
litematica_printer.config.comment.fluidS:
Set the working selection range rules for the printer in Fluid mode:
§dLitematica Selection§r: Use the full currently selected schematic selection as the working range
§dLitematica Render Layer§r: Only work within the current schematic render layer range
§dLitematica Selection (Below Player)§r: Only process areas below the player's height in the selection
§dLitematica Selection (Above Player)§r: Only process areas above the player's height in the selection
litematica_printer.config.comment.forced: Automatically sneak during printing to prevent accidental block interactions
litematica_printer.config.comment.invent: Whitelist of containers for the printer inventory; only containers in this list will be recorded
litematica_printer.config.comment.mine: Mine blocks within the selected area
litematica_printer.config.comment.mineSe:
Set the working selection range rules for the printer in Mine mode:
§dLitematica Selection§r: Use the full currently selected schematic selection as the working range
§dLitematica Render Layer§r: Only work within the current schematic render layer range
§dLitematica Selection (Below Player)§r: Only process areas below the player's height in the selection
§dLitematica Selection (Above Player)§r: Only process areas above the player's height in the selection (Default)
litematica_printer.config.comment.modeSw:
§dSingle Mode§r: Only one mode runs at a time.
§dMulti Mode§r: Multiple modes can run simultaneously.
You need to reopen the settings menu to see mode changes after switching.
litematica_printer.config.comment.multiB: When enabled, modes run by priority; lower priority modes cannot execute if higher priority modes are active
litematica_printer.config.comment.openSc: Hotkey to open the printer settings menu (the current interface)
litematica_printer.config.comment.print: Print blocks while holding the bound hotkey
litematica_printer.config.comment.printB: When enabled, break blocks that do not match the schematic during printing
litematica_printer.config.comment.printI: Place blocks directly without requiring a supporting block face
litematica_printer.config.comment.printW: Print water by placing ice and then breaking it
litematica_printer.config.comment.printe: Automatically disable the printer when you die to prevent unintended accidents

Automatically fill composters with compostable items.
(§lBe careful with your materials!§r)

When enabled, place regular logs first if stripped logs are unavailable, then use an axe to strip them to complete printing.
This saves time on manually stripping wood.
Automatically tune note blocks to the correct pitch during printing

Number of blocks printed per game tick when §6§lPrinter Speed§r is set to §b0§r. Higher values mean faster printing.
Set to §b0§r for no limit (may cause poor server performance); enable §6§lUse Packet Placement§r to mitigate this.
When enabled, break extra blocks that are not part of the schematic during printing

When enabled, break blocks that match the schematic type but have incorrect states during printing.
Examples: stairs/slabs with wrong orientation, vines/glowing vines on extra sides, etc.
Blocks that can be fixed by clicking (e.g., trapdoors, campfires, cherry clusters) will not be broken.
When enabled, check if the block below a falling block matches the schematic; if not, the falling block will not be placed

Item retrieval time increases if the target container is in an unloaded chunk. Press the hotkey after selecting a schematic area to set.
The printer will use items from this inventory during operation.
It is recommended to place a dummy to keep the chunk loaded.

Order of block traversal during printing:
§dXYZ§r: X-axis first, then Y-axis, finally Z-axis
§dXZY§r: X-axis first, then Z-axis, finally Y-axis
§dYXZ§r: Y-axis first, then X-axis, finally Z-axis
§dYZX§r: Y-axis first, then Z-axis, finally X-axis
§dZXY§r: Z-axis first, then X-axis, finally Y-axis
§dZYX§r: Z-axis first, then Y-axis, finally X-axis

Determines the shape used for block iteration:
§dCube§r: Iterate in a cube with side length equal to §6§lWorking Radius§r (recommended: 3).
§dSphere§r: Iterate in a sphere with radius equal to §6§lWorking Radius§r (recommended: 6).
Time interval (in milliseconds) used per game tick for iteration. Set to 0 to disable.

While the printer is working, check packet reception time. If no new packets are received for more than 20 game ticks,
the printer will pause automatically and resume once packets are received.

Working mode of the printer:
§dPrint§r: Restore blocks in the schematic (including block states like orientation, switches, etc.)
§dMine§r: Mine blocks within the selection (excludes fluids)
§dBedrock§r: Break bedrock within the selection using exploits (may only work under specific conditions)
§dFluid§r: Replace fluids in the selection with blocks from §6Fluid Replacement Block List§r
§dFill§r: Fill the selection with blocks from §6Fill Block List§r

§b§lTips:§r Except for §dPrint§r mode, the operation range is based on Litematica's selection.

When a block fails to place at the same position, wait for the set duration (in game ticks) before attempting to place again.
§c§lDo NOT set this to 0 - this may cause unexpected issues!§r

Retrieve items directly from shulker boxes in the inventory.
Replacement positions are Litematica's preset positions; if all preset positions have shulker boxes, no replacement will occur.

Cooldown time (in game ticks) for the Quick Shulker feature to prevent server lag from rapid shulker box opening.
Set to 0 to disable cooldown.

§dSimulate Click§r: Right-click the shulker box slot in the inventory to open it (requires server plugin support).
§dCall Mod§r: Directly call the QuickShulker mod to open shulker boxes (unavailable if QuickShulker is not installed).

Maximum placement distance (radius from the player's center). Higher values mean a larger printing range.
This parameter is linked to §6§lIterator Shape§r.
When set to 0, automatic delays are added to avoid orientation errors for blocks like pistons, sticky pistons, and observers.
Not recommended to set to 0 if printing redstone mechanisms.
Check if the block on the observer's detection face is correct before placing the observer (only place if correct)

Set the working selection range rules for the printer in Print mode:
§dLitematica Selection§r: Use the full currently selected schematic selection as the working range
§dLitematica Render Layer§r: Only work within the current schematic render layer range
§dLitematica Selection (Below Player)§r: Only process areas below the player's height in the selection
§dLitematica Selection (Above Player)§r: Only process areas above the player's height in the selection
When enabled, skip placing blocks that are waterlogged during printing

Interval time (in game ticks) between printing operations.
Set to 0 for no interval (may cause server lag).
Recommended to set between 1-5 to balance performance and speed.
When set to §b0§r, the §6§lBlocks per Tick§r option becomes available (reopen settings menu to see it).
Use packet sending instead of normal placement logic. Avoids "ghost blocks" in specific scenarios. §6§lNot recommended for general users.§r

Number of blocks processed per game tick.
Enabled when print interval is set to 0.
Recommended to set between 2-8 to balance performance and speed.
Setting too high may result in being kicked from the server.
When enabled, X-axis traversal will proceed from maximum to minimum values

When enabled, Y-axis traversal will proceed from maximum to minimum values.
Mining mode uses reverse direction by default; enabling this restores normal direction.
When enabled, Z-axis traversal will proceed from maximum to minimum values
litematica_printer.config.comment.putSki: When enabled, §6§lskip placing blocks in the Skip Placement List§r

You can enter a block ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:stone§r §bSandstone§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding blocks by tag), e.g.: §l#logs§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lGlazed Terracotta,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first).
litematica_printer.config.comment.render:
Display working mode and processed blocks (excludes fluid and fill modes) while the printer is working.
Also displays packet reception delay if §6§lLag Check§r is enabled.
Limit the printer's working range based on Litematica's render layer limit
litematica_printer.config.comment.replac: Print directly over blocks in the §6§lReplaceable Block List§r (e.g., grass, snow layers) without checking

When enabled, use live coral instead of dead coral if dead coral is unavailable in the inventory.
If both live and dead coral are present, dead coral will be prioritized for printing.

Ignore these incorrect blocks during printing and place directly over them.
You can enter a block ID or its translated name in the current language, e.g.: §bminecraft:stone§r §bSandstone§r.
If preceded by §b#§r, tag matching will be used (the list matches corresponding blocks by tag), e.g.: §l#logs§r.
If entering text with filter conditions (separated by English commas), e.g.: §lGlazed Terracotta,c§r.
Where “c” means using contains matching method (tries pinyin or direct match first).
litematica_printer.config.comment.storeO:
Attempt to return items retrieved from remote containers or quick shulkers to their original positions when the inventory is full.
Poor performance in 1.18.2 (may cause lag); recommended to disable.
litematica_printer.config.comment.syncIn:
Record items in the targeted container when the hotkey is pressed.
Sync items from identical container types in the schematic selection to the recorded container.
Hotkey to quickly enable/disable the container sync feature

Highlight color for container sync and printer inventory blocks.
Set to §l#00000000§r to disable highlight.
litematica_printer.config.comment.update: Check for updates when entering the world for the first time
litematica_printer.config.comment.useEas: When enabled, use easy place for block placement. No need to enable §6§lPrecise Placement§r when this is active.
litematica_printer.config.name.autoInven: Remote Interaction - Auto Enable Remote Access
litematica_printer.config.name.checkPlay: Core - Check Player Block Interaction Range
litematica_printer.config.name.printerIn: Remote Interaction - Set Printer Inventory Hotkey
litematica_printer.config.name.removePri: Remote Interaction - Clear Printer Inventory Hotkey
litematica_printer.config.name.replaceCo: Print - Replace Dead Coral with Live Coral
litematica_printer.config.name.syncInven: Remote Interaction - Sync Containers Toggle Hotkey
